{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Require annual reviews of all employers to identify and tackle discrimination",
        "additional_details": "We believe that not enough is done to enforce the Equality Act 2010 and that many people feel discriminated against and unsafe in their workplace. We believe this should change and that every workplace should be safe for people to work, without any fear of discrimination.",
        "background": "We want the Government to require the Equality and Human Rights Commission to conduct annual reviews of all employers, to ensure that there is no discrimination in the workplace, and take action if discriminatory actions are identified.",
